        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The right approach depends on whether anxiety is rooted in past trauma, ongoing life stress, or treatment-resistant patterns. EMDR is particularly effective when anxiety is driven by unprocessed memories or past experiences. CBT provides practical tools for managing the spiral in daily life. Ketamine-assisted therapy is available when anxiety has not responded to other treatments. The free consultation helps identify which path fits best."
